
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName false

class Aircraft {
  -name: String
  -type: String
  -yearOfManufacture: Integer
  -nextInspectionDate: Date
}

class Flight {
  -flightNumber: String
  -date: Date
}

class Passenger {
  -name: String
  -passportNumber: String
}

class Ticket {
  -ticketNumber: String
  -price: Double
  -upgradeDesired: Boolean
}

class PassengerAircraft {
  -numberOfSeats: Integer
}

class SeatCategory {
  -categoryDesignation: String
  -hasEntertainmentProgram: Boolean
  -numberOfSeats: Integer
}

class Airline {
  -name: String
}

class FlightAttendant {
  -name: String
  -dateOfEmployment: Date
  -isChiefSteward: Boolean
}

class Pilot {
  -name: String
  -dateOfEmployment: Date
  -license: String
}

class Airport {
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -numberOfRunways: Integer
}

Aircraft <|-- PassengerAircraft
PassengerAircraft "1" *-- "0..*" SeatCategory
FlightAttendant "1" *-- "0..*" Flight
Pilot "1" *-- "0..*" Flight
Aircraft "1" *-- "0..*" Flight
Flight "1" *-- "0..*" Passenger
Flight "1" *-- "1" Pilot
Flight "1" *-- "1..2" Pilot
Flight "1" *-- "0..*" FlightAttendant
Passenger "1" *-- "1" Ticket
Ticket "1" *-- "1" SeatCategory
Aircraft "1" *-- "0..1" Airport
Flight "1" *-- "1" Airport : departureAirport
Flight "1" *-- "1" Airport : destinationAirport
Aircraft "1" *-- "1" Airline
FlightAttendant "1" *-- "1" Airline
Pilot "1" *-- "1" Airline
@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- `Aircraft` is a general class, and `PassengerAircraft` inherits from it.
- A `PassengerAircraft` has multiple `SeatCategory` instances.
- Each `Flight` can have multiple `Passenger`s and one or more `Pilot`s (one captain, up to two co-pilots).
- Each `Passenger` has exactly one `Ticket`, which belongs to a specific `SeatCategory`.
- An `Aircraft` may be assigned to one `Airline`, and vice versa.
- `FlightAttendant`s and `Pilots` are employed by an `Airline`.

